metadata.description: Get Back Up is supposed to feel like a like a letter to my close friends and family. Music has always been an outlet where I have been able to a show a more vulnerable side of myself and talk about things I normally wouldn't share. Essentially what I'm saying in this song  is even though sometimes life can be hard, and I may feel defeated, I know that there's light at the end of the tunnel. My hope is that whoever hear's this song is able to apply it to their own personal situation and find the strength to keep pushing forward.

lyrics.text:
Verse 1:
I'm tired of feeling let down
Cause nothing seems to workout
It's hard for me to slow down
When I don’t even know how

Pre:
And I'm losing my patience
Hoping it will workout fine
Takin shots till I’m wasted
Only way to ease my mind
Cause as long as I can ease the pain
Maybe I won’t have to feel this way
And I know it wrong to numb my pain
But it’s the only way I know

Hook:
I'm up on a ledge 
Tryna find my way down
Turns out I’m depressed
Looking for a way out
I gave up on myself
And maybe I’m just bad luck
But I always seem to get back up
